HEADWORD: Pea jacket
<hw>Pea"
jack`et</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. D.
<ets>pij</ets>, <ets>pije</ets>, a coat of a coarse woolen stuff.]</ety>
<def>A thick loose double-breasted woolen jacket, or coat, commonly worn
by sailors in cold weather.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pea coat, peacoat, pea jacket.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>+ <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

